  ],
  "final_text": "Multiple ST-LINK probes are attached \u2014 let me find the right one.\nThe project targets the NUCLEO-L476RG, so I'll pin that probe:\nThe L4 SVD names instances directly \u2014 retrying with `SPI1`:\n**No \u2014 BSY is 0.** SPI1's status register reads clean, but the dump tells a bigger story:\n\n- **SR = 0x00000000** \u2192 `BSY=0`, no error flags (`OVR`/`MODF`/`CRCERR`/`TIFRFE` all 0), FIFOs empty.\n- **CR1 = 0x00000000** \u2192 `SPE=0` \u2014 the peripheral isn't even enabled. CR2 is also all zeros.\n\nOne caveat worth noting: SR's reset value on the L4 is `0x0002` (`TXE=1`), yet it reads **all-zero** here. That pattern is the classic signature of the **SPI1 peripheral clock being off** (RCC APB2ENR `SPI1EN=0`) \u2014 reads return 0 rather than real register state. So SPI1 isn't stuck busy; it's almost certainly never been clocked/initialized at all. That's consistent with this being the BLINKY firmware, which doesn't touch SPI.\n\nIf you want, I can read `RCC` next to confirm `APB2ENR.SPI1EN`."
}